<HL>
   Business Brief -- Chambers Development Co.:
   Firm to Buy Four Concerns
   That Collect Solid Waste
</HL>
<DATE>
09/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7B
</SO>
<CO>
   CDVA GLEN
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
POLLUTION CONTROL, WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES (POL)
</IN>
<LP>
   Chambers Development Co., Pittsburgh, said it will buy
four Georgia companies engaged in the collection and hauling
of commercial and residential solid waste. Terms weren't
disclosed.
   The acquisition of the four companies is expected to
generate annual revenue of $1.7 million. Global Environmental
Inc., Southern Waste Systems Inc. and Chadwick Enterprises
will be consolidated with Chambers' Atlanta operations, and
Dependable Garbage Service will be consolidated with
Chambers' Cedartown operations.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Chambers is an environmental concern offering services in
collection, hauling, disposal, recycling and landfill
development. Separately, Chambers said it received a permit
from the Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Resources
for its Fulkroad landfill in Dauphin County near Harrisburg.
Chambers plans to construct and operate about 15 acres of
landfill space at the facility.
</TEXT>
